               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-930" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-930" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-930" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-930" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BROWN</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at No. 16, Great Ormond-street, and am a labouring man. I let ready-furnished lodgings—I let the parlour to the prisoner about a month ago—she is a married woman—she had been there a fort night before the 5th of September—on the 6th, her husband told me that she took the sheet and the blanket—I then went and missed these things—a box of mine was broken that was in a room that I occupy, and from that I missed a hat, a bonnet, and cap of my wife's—there were four or five nails driven into the box, and it was opened.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-931" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-931" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-931" type="surname" value="MOORE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-931" type="given" value="JOHN JAMES"></interp>JOHN JAMES MOORE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. I have a hat, waistcoat, a bonnet, and cap—the hat and waistcoat were pawned by the prisoner—the others were pawned by a woman—I do not know by whom.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-932" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-932" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-932" type="surname" value="TUCKWOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-932" type="given" value="WILLIAM RICHARD"></interp>WILLIAM RICHARD TUCKWOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker, and have the teapot, flat-iron, sheet, and blanket—I do not know who pawned them, but the prisoner came in a state of intoxication, and wanted more money on them, which I refused—they were pawned in the name of Scanlan.</p>
               <p>
